## Details

- **Local URL**: `http://localhost:3000`
- **Dependencies**: all dependencies have been successfully installed.

## New Features

### Juz Viewing Context
The application was vastly expanded to enable users to view the Quran linearly by Juz. 
- Integrated a new **Juz** tab allowing selection from 1 to 30.
- Re-architected data structures and state representation to use unified `verseKey` (`Surah:Ayah`) tracking, gracefully allowing verses from multiple Surahs to coalesce cleanly on a single unified page.
- Inline Surah headers and Bismillah texts are intelligently rendered seamlessly during transitions between Surahs.

![Juz Viewing UI Demonstration](file:///D:/Users/JKDM/.gemini/antigravity/brain/7a2dc3ae-0b0f-4bfc-a233-ae91817447c2/juz_tab_preview_1772328261069.webp)

### Audio Playback
Added a new feature to play the audio recitation for each individual Ayah. 
- The Quran.com API `v4`'s recitation endpoint was integrated to fetch the audio URLs recursively for the viewed Surah (defaulting to the highly legible Mishary Rashid Alafasy).
- A specialized play/stop button was injected next to the bookmark action on every verse. It maintains exact playback state and ensures overlapping or multiple parallel recitations are safely halted before beginning a new one.

Here is a recording showcasing the audio playback feature across verses in Surah Al-Fatihah:
![Audio Playback Feature](file:///D:/Users/JKDM/.gemini/antigravity/brain/7a2dc3ae-0b0f-4bfc-a233-ae91817447c2/audio_playback_preview_1772327636007.webp)

### Quick Copy Ayah Content
Users can now instantly copy full Ayah context directly from the application with a single block:
- Formats a cleanly styled text segment placing Surah name and Verse number at the header.
- Appends the Arabic `uthmani` text beneath the header alongside its active language translation text ensuring ease of sharing.
- Employs the `navigator.clipboard` API enabling copies with a simple button layout near the play button.
- A temporary "Check" effect plays out on the icon indicating to the user their content is ready in their clipboard.

Recording showing the copy verification UI:
![Copy Ayah Action](file:///D:/Users/JKDM/.gemini/antigravity/brain/7a2dc3ae-0b0f-4bfc-a233-ae91817447c2/ayah_copy_preview_1772330588547.webp)

## Bug Fixes

- **Word-by-word translation language**: Fixed an issue where the word-by-word translation for Bahasa Melayu fell back to English. Since the Quran.com API (`v4`) does not support Malay word-by-word translations, we have mapped it to gracefully fallback to Indonesian (`id`), which is mutually intelligible and provides a much better experience than English.

Let me know if you would like me to make any modifications or if you have further requests!
